      • setExpiration

        T setExpiration(Date exp)
        Sets the JWT exp (expiration) timestamp. A null value will remove the property from the JSON map.

        A JWT obtained after this timestamp should not be used.

        the Claims instance for method chaining.

      • setIssuedAt

        T setIssuedAt(Date iat)
        Sets the JWT iat (issued at) timestamp. A null value will remove the property from the JSON map.

        The value is the timestamp when the JWT was created.

        Parameters:
        iat - the JWT iat value or null to remove the property from the JSON map.
        Returns:
        the Claims instance for method chaining.

      • setId

        T setId(String jti)
        Sets the JWT jti (JWT ID) value. A null value will remove the property from the JSON map.

        This value is a CaSe-SenSiTiVe unique identifier for the JWT. If specified, this value MUST be assigned in a manner that ensures that there is a negligible probability that the same value will be accidentally assigned to a different data object. The ID can be used to prevent the JWT from being replayed.

        Parameters:
        jti - the JWT jti value or null to remove the property from the JSON map.
        Returns:
        the Claims instance for method chaining.
